  "extraHighlightWords": [],
  "sentences": [
    {
      "en": "Sunday dinner at our house always follows the same rules, and Sophia enforces every single one of them.",
      "zh": "我們家的星期天晚餐永遠遵守同一套規矩，而且 Sophia 每一條都嚴格執行。"
    },
    {
      "en": "Rule one: everyone sits at the table together, no exceptions, not even for homework or robot costumes.",
      "zh": "第一條規矩：所有人一起坐在餐桌旁，沒有例外，就算有功課或機器人裝也一樣。"
    },
    {
      "en": "Rule two: you use a bowl for soup, a plate for rice, and a small dish for anything extra, never mix them up.",
      "zh": "第二條規矩：湯用碗裝、飯用盤子裝、額外的東西用小碟子裝，絕對不能搞混。"
    },
    {
      "en": "Rule three: chopsticks stay in your right hand, and a fork and knife only come out for special Western-style meals.",
      "zh": "第三條規矩：筷子要拿在右手，叉子跟刀只有在特別的西式餐點才會拿出來。"
    },
    {
      "en": "Tonight was one of those special nights, since Sophia cooked a piece of steak along with the usual rice and soup.",
      "zh": "今晚正好是那種特別的日子，因為 Sophia 除了平常的飯跟湯之外還煮了一塊牛排。"
    },
    {
      "en": "William tried to cut his steak with a spoon before anyone stopped him, and it did not go well at all.",
      "zh": "William 在被大家阻止之前試著用湯匙切牛排，結果當然完全不順利。"
    },
    {
      "en": "Sophia handed him a real fork and knife and reminded him, gently but firmly, to hold the knife with his right hand.",
      "zh": "Sophia 遞給他一副真正的叉子跟刀，溫柔但堅定地提醒他，刀要拿在右手。"
    },
    {
      "en": "Rule four: you must say \"please\" when you want something passed to you, and \"thank you\" right after you get it.",
      "zh": "第四條規矩：想要別人幫你拿東西的時候要說「請」，拿到之後馬上要說「謝謝」。"
    },
    {
      "en": "William asked, very politely, if someone could please pass the bread, and Dad handed it over with a proud smile.",
      "zh": "William 非常有禮貌地問能不能請大家幫忙傳一下麵包，爸爸帶著驕傲的笑容把麵包遞過去。"
    },
    {
      "en": "Rule five: no one is allowed to say a dish tastes bad, even if it does; you simply eat a little and stay quiet.",
      "zh": "第五條規矩：不准說一道菜難吃，就算真的難吃也一樣；你只要吃一點，然後保持安靜。"
    },
    {
      "en": "Tonight's soup was a little too salty, but everyone politely finished a full bowl without a single complaint.",
      "zh": "今晚的湯有點太鹹，但大家還是很有禮貌地喝完一整碗，一句抱怨也沒有。"
    },
    {
      "en": "Mom quietly refilled her glass of water three times, which was probably her honest opinion about the salt.",
      "zh": "媽媽默默地把水杯裝滿了三次，這大概就是她對這鹹度最誠實的意見。"
    },
    {
      "en": "Rule six: everyone shares whatever is on the table, and you never take the last piece without offering it around first.",
      "zh": "第六條規矩：桌上的東西大家一起分享，最後一塊食物在自己拿之前一定要先問一圈。"
    },
    {
      "en": "There was exactly one piece of steak left, and William offered it to me before I could even ask.",
      "zh": "剛好剩下一塊牛排，我還沒開口 William 就先讓給我了。"
    },
    {
      "en": "I was surprised, since sharing food is not usually his strongest skill, and I told him so directly.",
      "zh": "我有點驚訝，因為分享食物通常不是他最擅長的事，我也直接跟他這麼說了。"
    },
    {
      "en": "He said he was already full from two bowls of rice, so being generous today did not really cost him anything.",
      "zh": "他說他已經吃了兩碗飯很飽了，所以今天大方一點根本不用付出什麼代價。"
    },
    {
      "en": "Sophia overheard that and said real generosity should not depend on how full your own stomach already is.",
      "zh": "Sophia 聽到了，說真正的大方不應該取決於自己的肚子有多飽。"
    },
    {
      "en": "William thought about that for a second, then quietly gave me his last cookie too, without being asked.",
      "zh": "William 想了一下，然後主動把他最後一塊餅乾也給了我，沒人叫他這麼做。"
    },
    {
      "en": "Rule seven, the final and most important one, is that no one leaves the table until everyone is finished eating.",
      "zh": "第七條，也是最重要的一條：在所有人都吃完之前，誰都不准離開餐桌。"
    },
    {
      "en": "Perry does not officially have a seat at the table, but he waits under it very patiently every single night, just in case.",
      "zh": "Perry 正式來說沒有自己的座位，但他每天晚上都很有耐心地在桌子底下等著，以防萬一。"
    },
    {
      "en": "Tonight his patience finally paid off when a small piece of steak fell straight off William's plate and onto the floor.",
      "zh": "今晚他的耐心終於有了回報，一小塊牛排剛好從 William 的盤子上掉到地板上。"
    },
    {
      "en": "It disappeared in about one second, and none of us said a single word about it, because some rules are simply unspoken.",
      "zh": "牛排大概一秒鐘就消失了，我們沒有人講半句話，因為有些規矩本來就不用明講。"
    }
  ],
